    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-11-22T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-11-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="315"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d315">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Olney</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Somow</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-11-22">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 22, 1895</hi>.</date>
                    </dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 25.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the receipt of
                    your note of the 18th instant, advising me that your Government is willing to
                    consent to the application during the examination of the conditions of fur-seal
                    hunting of either one of the following measures the Government of the United
                    States may prefer: (1) Either that hunting on the open sea be completely
                    prohibited on all waters situated to the north of the thirty-fifth degree of
                    north latitude, (2) or that the provisions of the Paris award be applied to the
                    whole extent of Bering Sea.</p>
                <p>The Department is gratified to receive this amendment.</p>
                <p>Accept, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Richard Olney.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
